in guild for a port to a raid. <b>(edit Abin: Yes, you can ask us but, say, don't make us pick you up from a zone at Luclin. BE AT THE NEXUS!) </b> Simply do a /who GUILD Wizard or Druid then send a tell to one of those people. We may also be zoning at the time of tell so wait a couple minutes before you flip out in guild chat about no one wanting to port you to the raid.<br><br><b>- Be at a spire or circle BEFORE you ask for a port.</b> If you need a ride to a raid you're most likely one of many. I don't have time to run to Freeport, wait for you to finish a quest, or wait for you to ding an AA level. Be considerate and be ready for your port. If you ask for a port from one of us don't go AFK after you ask either.<br><br><b>-(edit Abin: Ports from others )</b>. Don't be afraid to ask for a port from a non-guild Wizard or Druid. If a raid has already started and you're late it's easier for you to have someone else out of guild to port you. This is important because most of us are bound in Luclin now and running from CS to ToV every 10 minutes is not fun. If after about 5-10 minutes of trying you can't find a port then ask us. I spend over 2kpp every ToV run; the least you can do is spend 100pp for a port. Don't use the excuse that people aren’t doing ports; I get them all the time for Rommy when he needs to get somewhere.  <br><br><b>The raid is over... how to get a trans!</b><br><br><b>- Wait until after all loot is distributed and be sure that no further plans are being made.</b> There is nothing more annoying than being OOM (which in most cases we all are after the mob dies) and getting spammed with translocate requests. The worst is when we start transing impatient people only to pick them up later since we end up doing something else.<br><br><b>- Send a tell to a Wizard for a trans. Send a tell to a Wizard / Druid for a port.</b> Most of us "/gu Send tells for (insert destinations here)" so only ask for those destinations. Send a tell, don't ask in guild or say because chances are we're not watching those channels.<br><br><b>- Don't concentrate all of your trans tells at one Wizard. </b>It's very rare to find one Wizard on our raids so don't spam one person with trans requests.<br><br><b>- When asking for a trans, send a tell with the destination you want.</b> People who send tells "trans me plz" get ignored from now on.  I'm not a psychic and I doubt the other Wizards are. Don't say "I don't care where I go" either, pick a location please! My alternative personality is not Miss Cleo!<br><b>(edit Abin: I can't stress this one enough. Do NOT JUST SAY "TL me plz" - have a destination in mind. It saves me time memming TLs for everyone)</b><br><br><b>- Be near or next to me when you ask for a trans.</b><i> I use /target to invite people into my translocate group!</i> DO NOT BE on the other side of the room when I ask, I'm not running around to find you for a trans.  <br><br><b>- Disband from your group prior to asking for a trans.</b> It's annoying when you get a tell from someone asking for a trans, you invite them, and they are in another group.<br><br><b>- Be attentive when getting a trans.</b> Inviting you to my group for a trans != go AFK to feed your goldfish. WATCH the screen and be ready to click yes. Translocate boxes stay up for a total of around 15 seconds and if you asked for a trans that requires a fragment (will get to this later) and the box poofs, you've just wasted one of my fragments.<br><br><b>- Wait until we're done with the transes we shout in guild until you ask for somewhere different.</b> This drives me crazy! If you want to go to Great Divide and we're doing transes to DL/Gfay/Bind at the moment, wait until we're done doing those before you ASK to go somewhere else. Want a port to somewhere we can't trans to? Don't ask us for a trans, /t a Druid who is on the raid. <br><br><b>List of Translocate Destinations:<br>A "*" indicates that this trans requires a component.<br><br>- Greater Faydark<br>- North Karana<br>- Tox<br>- Dreadlands<br>- The Nexus (only works on Luclin)<br>- Bind Point<br>- In-Zone (moves you to the "safe spot")<br>- Cobalt Scar*<br>- Great Divide*<br>- Iceclad*<br>- Wakening Lands*<br>- Cazic-Thule*<br>- West Karana*<br>- North Ro*<br>- Nektulos Forest*<br>- West Commons*<br><br>- There is NO Skyfire / Emerald Jungle trans.<br>- There is (edit Abin:)NO SOUTH RO TRANS!!!.</b><br><br><b>How to obtain Portal Fragments:</b><br><br>(edit Abin)<br>From the gnome vendor on the 2nd floor in The Temple of Solusek Ro. <br><br>That’s about it. Feel free to comment or whatever but please try and use this guideline when asking for a port to a raid or a trans after one.<br>__________________________________________<br><br> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40529>Abinsuran Autishzaar</A><br>Sorceror&#8729;<br>Proud member of Walkers&#8729;<br> Vazaelle Server&#8729;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br> <font color=#00F500>(2/12/02 11:48:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=466.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Raid Porting Guide</span><hr size=1> Please please please mention destination up front, and if you don't know where you want to go yet, don't ask until you do. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-banner-long-3b.gif" height=60 width=468 alt="Whizbang Dustyboots" border=0></a><br><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/bottom.gif" height=12 width=239 alt="an e